snippet.textDisplay: ...Launch control, ALS, shift lights... so many freaking systems we didn't know about or didn't need 20 years ago. Back then you literally had to know and feel your car for a perfect start and race. High rpm at the ideal launchspot (best whilst stepping on the brake to have max load), releasing the clutch when the engine turns up, double-clutch, changing gears at perfect BHP and off you go! Back then 1/4 mile was sport and only the best drivers won. Nowadays the kids stall their engines, launch at low rpm and then telling everybody the systems won't work...
